# TRANSFORMER_BEGIN MANUAL_GEOSPATIAL_SETTER_NG,1,"""FGP Tools""",dad04ad3-aa7c-4663-93f6-ef1d6421baef,"Linked by Default",No,NO_PARALLELISM,,No,25241,YES,No,313,No,
# <p><strong>Description </strong></p>
# <p>This custom transformer sets manually the spatial representation type.  The supplied lookup table contains the ID and the spatial representation type for a subset of the metadata records.</p>
# <p><strong>Input Ports </strong></p>
# <p>LOOKUP_TABLE_INPUT: Input information from the lookup table</p>
# <p>DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.</p>
# <p><strong>Output Ports </strong></p>
# <p>GEOSPATIAL: Output port for the geospatial metadata records</p>
# <p>NON-GEOSPATIAL: Output port for the non geospatial metadata records</p>
# <p>UNMAPPED_DATA: Output port for the metadata records for which the spatial representation type cannot be determine.</p>
# <p><strong>Parameters </strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>
# <p>FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;</p>
# </li>
# <li>
# <p>P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.</p>
# </li>
# </ul>
# TRANSFORMER_END
